<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Obit-Norden     09-22 0198</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Obit-Norden,0204</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Christine Norden, One-Time British Sex Symbol, Dead At Age 63</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actress Christine Norden, a one-time British sex
symbol who was the first performer to appear topless in a Broadway
play, died Wednesday at age 63, her agent said.
   Vincent Shaw said Miss Norden died at West Middlesex Hospital
following a heart attack that came two months after a double
heart-bypass operation in July.
   Miss Norden, born Molly Thornton in the northern England town of
Sunderland, began her career in the 1940s under contract to London
Films and Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer.
   Her films included ``Night Beat,'' ``Mine Own Executioner,''
``Idol of Paris'' and ``Reluctant Heroes'' before she moved to New
York in 1953.
   She made her Broadway debut in 1960 in the musical
``Tenderloin'' and later made headlines by being the first Broadway
actress to appear on-stage topless in the 1967 comedy ``Scuba
Duba,'' which also starred Jerry Orbach.
   She last appeared on the British stage in a 1979 revival of
``The Marriage Go Round,'' and had a small role in the 1986 movie
musical ``Little Shop of Horrors.''
   She is survived by her fifth husband, George Heselden, a
scientist for the Ministry of Defense.
</TEXT>
