<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0432</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Storms Rip Roofs in Texas</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Showers and thunderstorms fell from Kansas to Texas today after
strong storms that ripped the roofs off buildings in Texas with
winds gusting to 60 mph and caused flash flooding in New Mexico.
   A thunderstorm in the Texas Panhandle on Wednesday evening tore
roofs off some buildings near Dalhart. In Dell City in southwest
Texas, another thunderstorm also produced gusts to 60 mph.
   In southeastern New Mexico, thunderstorms Wednesday evening
produced flash flooding between Carlsbad and Artesia.
   Showers and thunderstorms also fell today from northern Iowa to
eastern Wisconsin. Dry weather prevailed across the rest of the
nation.
   Skies were cloudy from the Southwest to the upper Mississippi
Valley and middle and northern Atlantic Coast. Clear skies
prevailed over the rest of the country.
   Today's forecast called for scattered showers and thunderstorms
from eastern Kansas to eastern Iowa, most of Illionis and the Great
Lakes states, and over the central and southern Rockies and
northern Arizona; showers in the lower Great Lakes states; and
mostly sunny skies in the rest of the country.
   High temperatures were expected to be in the 60s from North
Dakota to the upper Mississippi Valley, northern Great Lakes and
northern New England, as well as in most of Utah, northern Arizona,
the Pacific Northwest and along the California Coast; the 90s in
most of the southern Plains, the lower Mississippi Valley, the Gulf
Coast, Alabama, Georgia and Florida; and in the 70s and 80s in the
rest of the nation.
   Temperatures around at the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 34
degrees at Yellowstone National Park, Wyo., to 82 degrees at the
Corpus Christi, Texas, Naval Air Station and Dallas.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 62 fair; Boston 63 partly cloudy; Buffalo 55
cloudy; Charleston, S.C. 68 fair; Cincinnati 53 partly cloudy;
Cleveland 57 cloudy; Detroit 54 partly cloudy; Miami 75 fair; New
York 62 fair; Philadelphia 62 cloudy; Pittsburgh 56 cloudy;
Portland, Maine 61 cloudy; Washington 61 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 38 fair; Chicago 61 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
79 fair; Denver 52 fair; Des Moines 76 fair; Indianapolis 57 fair;
Kansas City 76 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 60 cloudy; Nashville 56
fair; New Orleans 76 fair; St. Louis 72 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 56 fair; Anchorage 40 partly cloudy; Las
Vegas 60 fair; Los Angeles 61 fair; Phoenix 70 fair; Salt Lake City
53 cloudy; San Diego 61 fair; San Francisco 56 fair; Seattle 50
fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 50 partly cloudy; Toronto 55 partly cloudy.
</TEXT>
