<HEAD>K mart Recalls Scissors Desk Sets</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: CORRECTS K Mart to K mart throughout.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Some 48,000 scissors desk sets that could pose
a hazard to children are being recalled by K mart Corp., the
Consumer Product Safety Commission announced today.
   The ``School Days Scissors Desk Set,'' includes a razor blade
cutting knife that could pose a danger to children, the agency
said. The set sold for less than $1 in K mart stores during July
and included the scissors, pencil sharpener and the cutting knife.
   Parents should remove the set from use by children and return it
to the nearest K mart for a refund, the commission said.
   Persons needing more information can contact the commission at
1-800-638-2772.
