<HEAD>New Citibank Visa Customer Finds That Later Is Relatively Sooner</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: `Maube' is cq</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Visa card applicant who replied, ``Maybe
later,'' when asked if she wanted a second card for a relative got
a laugh when her card came with a second one imprinted with the
name Maube Later.
   But Citibank, which issued the card, wasn't laughing.
   ``Are you serious?'' bank spokeswoman Susan Weeks asked when
contacted about the incident by telephone in New York. Citibank is
the nation's largest bank and the world's biggest issuer of Visa
and MasterCard credit cards.
   ``I can't wait to hear the explanation on this,'' Ms. Weeks said
after vowing to get to the bottom of the incident.
   Doris Stokes, an assistant administrator at the Los Angeles
Junior Chamber of Commerce, said she wasn't the only one to chuckle
at the card. She said she had applied for the card by telephone
recently.
   ``I brought it down to work, and everybody there was in tears
laughing so hard about it,'' Ms. Stokes said.
