<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--ShoemakerSuicide     09-22 0153</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Shoemaker Suicide,0156</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Shoemaker Burns To Death In Pile Of Burning Goods</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAGOS, Nigeria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A roadside shoemaker jumped into a pile of
blazing goods and burned to death after sanitation men seized his
wares and set them afire, witnesses said Thursday.
   The witnesses said the shoemaker, whose name was not available,
had collected enough capital as a beggar to set himself up with a
roadside shop.
   A team of sanitation workers, enforcing a ban on street trading,
raided the Yaba commercial district where the shoemaker worked. The
traders fled, watching from a distance as the officials began
burning their wares.
   Witnesses, including a Nigerian radio correspondent, said the
shoemaker ran and jumped into the fire before anyone could stop
him. Hundreds of shoppers and traders watched as he died.
   The street trading ban was imposed to reduce congestion on the
streets of this city of more than 4 million people.
</TEXT>
