<2ND_LINE>PM-Gang Rape, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0545,0548</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Tearful Victim Testifies In Gang Rape Trial</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Leads with 7 grafs to UPDATE with woman's testimony, edit,
picking up 7th graf pvs, `The woman ....' Note contents.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By JOEL WILLIAMS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>SAN DIEGO, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A tearful woman, clutching a stuffed
animal, broke down on the witness stand today after testifying that
she was raped and sodomized by a group of men.
   ``I was screaming and telling him to stop. ... He was holding my
legs. I was trying to push him off,'' the 19-year-old woman said of
defendant Orlando Garza, 23, the first to be tried of the 10 men
indicted in the case.
   She said Garza was laughing as he raped her on the hood of a
car, and that other men nearby joined in and also sexually
assaulted her. After she had testified for about one hour, the
court recessed when the woman, in tears, said she was about to
faint.
   On Wednesday, the doctor who examined the woman said she was
scratched and bruised, including internal bruises, when she arrived
at a hospital for treatment.
   ``She told me she had been sexually assaulted by as many as 20
to 23 men,'' said Dr. Vilma Garcia, who examined her at Humana
Hospital-Corpus Christi on March 27.
   The woman said ``that they were her neighbors,'' Garcia
testified Wednesday in the sexual assault trial.
   Assistant District Attorney Rodolfo Gutierrez said he expected
the woman to continue her testimony later today.
   The woman, who was a resident of San Diego at the time, told
authorities she was kidnapped and sexually assaulted by the men
over a period of several hours on the night of March 26-27.
   All 10 have pleaded innocent to charges including kidnapping,
aggravated kidnapping and sexual assault.
   ``This was not a kidnapping,'' defense attorney Albert Pena said
in an interview Wednesday. ``She voluntarily went.''
   Jose Carlos Briones testified Wednesday that the woman scratched
her attackers, cried out for help and fainted while she was being
raped on the hood of a car outside town.
   Briones, 29, said the woman cried: ``Help me, please help me.''
   ``She was moaning and groaning. She had tears in her eyes,''
Briones said in Spanish through an interpreter.
   ``I was the only one who told them to leave her alone,'' said
Briones, who also faces a sexual assault charge in the case.
   Prosecutors have promised to recommend probation for Briones in
exchange for his testimony. Briones says he was impotent at the
time of the attack from drinking too much beer.
   When Pena asked him if the woman was making sounds of pleasure,
Briones answered: ``It was nothing about being happy.''
   He said Garza held the woman's wrists during part of the attack.
   ``He (Garza) told me to hold her because she was scratching
him,'' Briones said.
   Briones said he saw several of the other defendants assaulting
the woman.
   Sexual assault is punishable by two to 20 years in prison and-or
a fine of up to $10,000.
   The woman, her husband and two children have moved to an
undisclosed location in another city because of reported harassment
since she accused the 10 men.
</TEXT>
