<HEAD>Bush Tops Dukakis in New Hampshire Poll</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Political Rdp Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANCHESTER, N.H. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   New Hampshire voters prefer Republican
George Bush over Democrat Michael Dukakis by a better than 2-1
margin, a new presidential poll indicates.
   Fifty-eight percent of the 397 likely New Hampshire voters
surveyed favored Bush and 26 percent support Dukakis, according to
the University of New Hampshire poll conducted for the Boston Globe
and station WMUR-TV in Manchester.
   Dukakis faces a tough race in the state because Republicans edge
Democrats in voter registration, according to university pollster
David Moore.
   The telephone poll, conducted Sept. 14-18, has a margin of error
of four percentage points.
