<HEAD>More Than 100 Die In Flood</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES thruout with 106 deaths.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>KATMANDU, Nepal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A flash flood ripped through a mountain
village and killed more than 100 people, including four policemen,
authorities said Thursday.
   Home Ministry officials confirmed the deaths of 106 people and
said the toll may still be higher because several visitors spent
the night in the area Tuesday.
   The officials said at least 58 people lost their lives in
Darwang village, 125 miles west of Katmandu, and 48 others died in
nearby Niskot.
   Only four bodies have been recovered. Rescuers were searching
for others.
   The flood began Tuesday night when a boulder broke loose from a
landslide that dammed the Myagdi River and created a huge lake.
