<1ST_LINE>u f BC-AutoProdn     09-22 0150</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Auto Prodn,0157</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Production Goes Up This Week</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Only version planned.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
232,547 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
231,752, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
in which 212,046 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 146,940 cars this week,
compared with 143,388 a week ago and 137,765 in the same week in
1987.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 85,607,
compared with last week's 88,364 and last year's 74,281.
   Canadian automakers were to build 20,697 cars this week, down
from 20,701 a week ago but up from last year's 15,953.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 21,925,
compared with 21,690 a week ago and 19,165 in the same week last
year.
</TEXT>
